{
    "id": "541",
    "title": "Maximum Allowable Blood Loss (ABL) Without Transfusion",
    "desc": "The Maximum Allowable Blood Loss (ABL) estimates the maximum allowable blood loss intraoperatively before transfusion should be considered, based on initial hemoglobin, weight and final hemoglobin.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/6829965",
                "text": "Gross JB. Estimating Allowable Blood Loss Corrected for Dilution. Anesthesiology 58.2 (1983): 277-280."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [],
        "evidence": "<p>ABL = [EBV x (H<sub>i</sub>-H<sub>f</sub>)] / H<sub>av</sub>, where EBV = body weight, kg x average blood volume*, mL/kg and other variables are as follows:</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Variable</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td><strong>Description</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>ABL</td>\n<td>\n<p>Allowable blood loss</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>EBV</td>\n<td>\n<p>Estimated blood volume</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>H<sub>i</sub></td>\n<td>\n<p>Initial hemoglobin</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>H<sub>f</sub></td>\n<td>\n<p>Final hemoglobin (cutoff for transfusion)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>H<sub>av</sub></td>\n<td>\n<p>Average of initial and final hemoglobin</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*Average blood volume by age:</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Age</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Average blood volume, mL/kg</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Adult man</td>\n<td>\n<p>75</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Adult woman</td>\n<td>\n<p>65</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Infant</td>\n<td>\n<p>80</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Neonate</td>\n<td>\n<p>85</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Premature neonate</td>\n<td>\n<p>96</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p></p>",
